                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#161r" facs="165">Fol. 161r</locus><desc>Crude drawings in pencil of two faces (Madonna and Child?); faint</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#162r" facs="166">Fol. 162r</locus><desc>Crude drawing in pencil of a figure</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3"><locus target="#162v" facs="167">Fol. 162v</locus><desc>Crude drawing in pencil of two figu</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d4">
                      Decorative designs:
                      <locus target="#1r #144r" facs="005 148">folss. 1r, 144r, </locus> (ḥaräg);
                      <locus target="#8r #15v #23r #33v #41r #47v #136v" facs="012 020 027 038 045 052 141">8r, 15v, 23r, 33v, 41r, 47v, 136v, </locus> (a line of alternating red and black dots);
                      <locus target="#83v #96v #108r #117r" facs="088 101 112 121">83v, 96v, 108r, 117r, </locus> (a line of red dots);
                      <locus target="#123v #156r #160v" facs="128 160 165">123v, 156r, 160v</locus> (multiple full stops</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                    <list>
                      <item xml:id="e1"><desc><locus target="#ir(ecto) #iv(erso) #iir(ecto) #iiiv(erso) #ivr(ecto) #161r #162r #162v" facs="001 002 004 165 166 167">Fols. ir(ecto), iv(erso), iir(ecto), iiiv(erso), ivr(ecto), 161r, 162r, 162v</locus> scrawls and pen trials</desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="a1"><desc type="OwnershipNote"><locus target="#iiv(erso) #iir(ecto)" facs="003 002">Fols. iiv(erso), iir(ecto)</locus> Note of ownership: “This Psalter belongs to Kahǝsay Wäldä Kidan.” </desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="a2"><desc type="RecordTransaction"><locus target="#iiir(ecto)" facs="003">Fol. iiir(ecto)</locus> in blue pen. Note of transaction: “From Wäldä Maryam Bärǝhe, Qes Ḥagos and friend, received one birr.” </desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="a3"><desc><locus target="#ivv(erso)" facs="005">Fol. ivv(erso)</locus> Note in crude hand by Tigriñña speaker: “The scribe of this book is Täklä Wäldä Kidan.  I brought it from Mämǝḥre Kahǝsay.  His wife told me to give three schillings.” </desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="e2"><desc><locus target="#63r" facs="067">Fol. 63r</locus> a line of black dots and a symbol in the margin mark the midpoint of the psalms. </desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="a4"><desc><locus target="#160v" facs="165">Fol. 160v</locus> Note from scribe: “Glory to Father, Son and Holy Spirit who helped me to finish in peace.” </desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="e3"><desc>Psalm 118 is marked with the (Hebrew) letter written in red ink at the head of the section.</desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="e4"><desc>
                        words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#22v #38r #111r #111v" facs="027 042 115 116">folss. 22v, 38r, 111r, 111v, </locus>, etc.);
                        erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#48v #67r #85v" facs="053 071 090">48v, 67r, 85v, </locus>, etc.);
                        text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#20v #89r" facs="025 093">20v, 89r</locus>)</desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="e5"><desc>
                        The scribe’s chosen aspect ratio for the codex combined with the script size forces the scribe to reduce the font size at the end of
                        lines to avoid having to go onto the next line throughout the codex. But, wher"e the line of text is still too long, the scribe completes
                        the line of text above the end of the line (e.g., <locus target="#7v #67r #70v" facs="012 071 075">fols. 7v, 67r, 70v</locus>).</desc></item>
                    </list>
                  </additions>
